  <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
  <p>The Privacy Policy of the User's personal data (hereinafter referred to as the "Policy") applies to all websites, portals, services, applications, programs and products of "Roomp" LLC (hereinafter referred to as "Roomp Services") and / or its affiliates, including all persons belonging to the same group as "Roomp" LLC (collectively referred to as "Company Roomp".) The consent of the User to the Policy expressed by him within the framework of interaction with one of the participants of the group, applies to all others as well.</p>&nbsp;

  <p>By using Roomp Services, you agree to our privacy policy laid out herein and the terms of processing your personal data; the User should refrain from using Roomp Services in case of disagreement with these conditions.</p>
  <p>User's personal data is proceeded in accordance with the Federal Law "On Personal Data" No. 152.</p>&nbsp;

  <p>By providing Roomp personal data using Roomp Services, the User agrees to it being proceeded and used to fulfill the provisions of "Terms and Conditions" (Public Offer) as well as to promote Roomp products and services, control the results of advertising campaigns / promotions, customer support, demand studies, and User's behavior, preferences and satisfaction.</p><br>
  <p>The User also agrees that the information he furnished is true, complete and correct and does not violate Federal Law. In case of violating Federal Law or furnishing wrongful, incomplete or unauthorized information, Roomp shall not be liable for User's actions and the provided information.</p>&nbsp;

  <p>Roomp and Roomp Services may process the following personal data of the User: First Name, Last Name, Patronymic, phone number, e-mail address, and date of birth.</p>&nbsp;

  <p>By processing personal data we mean any action (operation) or a combination of actions (operations) performed both automatically and manually with personal data, including collection, recording, arrangement, accumulation, storage, specification (updating, changing), extraction, use, distribution (including transfer), anonymizing, blocking and destruction of personal data.</p>&nbsp;

  <p>Roomp carries out the procession of the personal data of the User on its own, but it can be transferred to third parties in the following cases:</p>&nbsp;<ol>
    <li>The accommodating facility that was booked by the User
    </li>
    <li>Roomp's company office to provide a better User's support
    </li>
    <li>Third-party service providers to simplify the processes of booking, analysis and distribution of promotional materials.
      <strong>Third parties cannot use personal data of the User for their own purposes or any other purposes</strong><strong>.</strong></li>
    <li>Competent authorities (government authorities) for the prevention, detection or prosecution of criminal acts and fraud.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <p>Roomp has the right to send out information, including advertising messages, to the User's e-mail and mobile phone with the consent, expressed through his actions, uniquely identifying the User and allowing to reliably establish his desire to receive messages.</p>&nbsp;<p>
    The User has the right to opt out of receiving promotional and other information without giving any reasons for the refusal by informing Roomp either by calling {{__("header.support_phone")}} or sending an email to help@roomp.co. Service messages informing the User about booking and using other Roomp services and products are generated automatically and cannot be rejected by the User.</p>
  <p>Roomp does not use the Roomp Services User's IP address to identify the User.</p>&nbsp;<p>Roomp Services use data collection devices such as "cookies" on certain pages of the Site to help analyze our web page flow, measure promotional effectiveness, and promote trust and safety. We also use cookies to allow you to enter your password less frequently during a session. Cookies can also help us provide information that is targeted to your interests. You are always free to decline our cookies if your browser permits, although in that case you may not be able to use certain features on the Site. "Cookies" do not contain any private information.</p>&nbsp;

  <p>Roomp has the right to record telephone conversations with the User. At the same time, Roomp undertakes to prevent attempts to unauthorized access to information obtained during telephone conversations and / or transfer it to third parties not directly related to the execution of Orders, in accordance with cl. 16 of the Federal Law "On Information, Information Technologies and Information Protection.".</p>&nbsp;

  <p>The User does not have the right to resell, create external hyperlinks, use, copy, monitor, display, download or reproduce any part of the content or information, software, products or services provided on our site for any commercial or competing activity or purpose.</p>&nbsp;

  <p>Please note that our privacy policy is subject to change at any time without notice. Therefore, you may periodically review this page to make sure you have the latest version of the privacy policy.</p>&nbsp;

  <p>If you have any questions and concerns regarding Privacy Policy or privacy related issues, do not hesitate to contact us by calling {{__("header.support_phone")}} or sending out an email to help@roomp.co.</p>

